data.description: 78 acre, 4BR 3.5 BA, Thoughtfully developed 78 acre property with Broad River frontage, approximately 4 miles of trails, hunting/fishing, abundant hardwood tree varieties, clear cut lumber income opportunity, in-ground salt-water swimming pool, all with a secluded custom home situated in the center of the 78 acre estate. The details and opportunities of enjoyment this property has to offer families are plenty. Choose from hunting, fishing, ATV trails, gardening, kayaking on the Broad River, large family gatherings, relaxing by the pool and more. Some existing features of the land to highlight are multiple deer stands, several food plots, shooting range, 4 beaver ponds, wide/lengthy/cleared trails and wild berries for picking. The home is situated in the middle of 78 acres roughly 1/2 mile off the road and offers a peaceful setting with beauty/nature/privacy to surround you. The home accommodates country living and spacious entertaining. The chef'sj kitchen is open to a breakfast/keeping room that has many windows letting the beautiful outside in. The kitchen features custom cabinets, granite countertops, stainless appliances, two ovens, built in microwave, dishwasher, disposal and walk-in pantry. The split floor plan has a large master suite, attached bath includes large custom double vanity cabinets, soaking tub, oversize multi-head shower, spacious closet and outside access to the expansive rear deck. The two additional bedrooms on the main level are connected with a Jack-N-Jill bath. Located in the basement is a spacious 4th bedroom, additional full bath and private entrance. The property is a host to a variety of wildlife which hunters can enjoy. Previously, the trees have been harvested which does provide potential income. House extras include the in-ground salt-water pool, oversize attached 2 car garage for larger sized trucks, designated office for at home professionals, 2 fireplaces with gas start, irrigation system, underground water drainage, gas grill lines located at deck level, all underground utilities from the road, security system, ample storage, approximately 2,800 sqft unfinished 9' ceiling basement and a deep well w/ water filtration system. Recently updated HVAC, water heater and painted exterior. The basement is plumbed for a future kitchen/bar area or other desired finished living space. There is a site previously cleared and prepped with water, electric, and cable underground for a Barn/garage. Potential for home buyers to fence open/cleared areas for horses or livestock. Country living not too far from Athens GA, 20 min drive to town and 30 min to UGA. The home is nicely secluded in the middle of 78 acre, is private and seen by appointment only. Bring proper footwear to tour this land.
